        <abstract>
            <p>Mentions the difficulties in explaining the separation of sexes and Carl Nägeli’s view that the sexes of plants were primordially distinct.</p>
            <p>Has been experimenting for five or six years to demonstrate that the benefits of crossing are the same as those derived from a slight change of conditions.</p>
        </abstract>
